	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a Wood Elf Tailor and a Druid as soon as I made this tunic, which was about 1 week ago, I sold off my Foreman's Tunic. I did this for several reasons:<br>1 - Foreman's Tunic is nice until about level 19-24 when Druid's realize that they should be acting as a caster and not as a tank like so many want to. Let's fact it - Bard's should know from the start that they should sit in the background, along with Clerics.<br>2 - STR...much better Chest items out there for Warrior, Paladain and Rogue's than this with a lot higher AC. For Druid's, Bard's, Cleric's see item 1.<br>3 - CHA - What more could a Druid ask for? CHA and WIS on the same item! And it's less than 1kpp. Very nicely done. Bard's love CHA too and considering the price it's not a bad alternative - provided you are not twinked out by your guild with Lambent.<br>4 - AC - To be honest, since the +STAT changes don't make a large difference until post level 30 +2AC is much nicer than +3STR. Oh, if your still wearing this or Foreman's Tunic after level 30 get into a good group and hunt for better armor.<br><br>Blackscale and Ammdar I totally aggree with you on this. This armor is a great alternative. And costing only 40pp-ish to make is a good profit for all the pp sunk into tailoring.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ayamaki Treestar<br>Tholuxe Paells Server<br>Master Baker, Brewer, Smithe, Potter, Tailor, Fletcher</td></tr>
