	   <tr><td colspan=2>It looks like normal leather armor.<br><br>And speaking as the guy who submitted it, while it's not as good as a foreman's tunic for wisdom, it's a LOT cheaper to make.<br><br>Foreman's is 0 weight, 10 ac, 3 str, 3 wis; It costs around 200pp on one server I play on (Xev) and around 250pp on the other I play on (Erollisi Marr).<br><br>Imbued Mithril Reinforced is 2.5 weight, 12 ac, 2 wis, 3 cha; Cost to make it was just over 40pp, and I have sold these for 125pp.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a side note, charisma is rather useful to druids, especially those fighting in Velious, as most of a druid's animal-specific spells (fear, charm, lull) are charisma based (just like with an enchanter).<br><br>So it's arguably better for a druid than a Foreman's tunic, if you fight a lot of animals.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
